// Dense 16x16 Haar-random 4-qubit unitary (scipy unitary_group.rvs,
// random_state=13). Exercising the recursive Quantum Shannon Decomposition for
// a 4-qubit custom operation. Numerical correctness is verified by CircuitCheck
// (rebuild the synthesized unitary and compare it to this matrix); the rotation
// angles are gauge/sign dependent across platform LAPACK builds, so they are not
// pinned with FileCheck.
//
// KAK sub-decompositions can produce different (but equivalent) gate sequences on
// macOS due to platform-specific math libraries.
// UNSUPPORTED: system-darwin
// RUN: cudaq-opt --unitary-synthesis --canonicalize --apply-op-specialization --aggressive-inlining %s | CircuitCheck %s

